text: Limnonectes isanensis is a species of fanged frogs in the family Dicroglossidae. It was discovered in Phu Luang Wildlife Sanctuary, Loei Province, Thailand in 2012. It belongs to the Limnonectes kuhlii species complex.McLeod, Kelly & Barley (2012). “Same-same but different”: Another new species of the Limnonectes kuhlii complex from Thailand (Anura: Dicroglossidae).
